Installation
1) Install Visual Studio Code: https://code.visualstudio.com/
2) Install Git: https://git-scm.com/downloads
3) Install Python: https://www.python.org/downloads/
4) Open command prompt
5) Choose or create project location folder:
cd folder path | mkdir folder name
6) Clone mpk repository:
git clone https://github.com/kod3ch/django-mpk.git
7) Choose mpk folder: cd django-mpk
8) Create virtual environment: python -m venv venv
9) Activate virtual environment: .\venv\Scripts\activate
10) Install Django: pip install Django
11) Install Django tweaks widget: pip install django-widget-tweaks
12) Check all installed packages: pip list
13) Open Visual Studio Code
14) Press Ctrl+K+O than open mpk folder
15) Select Python interpreter:
press Ctrl+Shift+P
type Python:Select Interpreter
select
select
16) Run the server: python manage.py runserver
17) Open your browser and type: http://127.0.0.1:8000/
18) Press Ctrl+C to quit the server
19) Deactivate virtual environment: .\venv\Scripts\deactivate
20) Close command prompt
21) Close Visual Studio Code
